  "texts": [
    "However, in a prospective trial comparing AI to dermatologists in a teledermatology setting, dermatologists outperformed the AI (13).",
    "Despite AI currently underperforming dermatologists, AI could provide a new perspective that could still be beneficial as AI and humans exhibit distinct types of errors.",
    "For instance, models may provide insights into certain images' classification ambiguity, whereas humans are better able to distinguish variability in image quality such as blurriness or shadowing (12).",
    "Augmented intelligence can also assist with suggesting clinical decisions given inputted images, such as recommending whether a lesion warrants excision (34).",
    "The integration of AuI into dermatologic patient management resulted in a 19.2% reduction in unnecessary excisions of benign lesions (35)."
  ],
